tafsir[24]{c,v,t}:
  95,1,"Fig (Tin) and Olive (Zaytun) are the names of two hills in the vicinity of  Jerusalem  where Jesus’s field of action was situated. Mount Sinai (Tur Sinin) refers to that hill where God made His revelation to Moses. The ‘secure land’ (al-Baladu’l Amin) refers to Makkah where the Prophet Muhammad was born."
